                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17956</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Letcher</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-21T11:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 21, 1916, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to removal Colonel Brown to Adela to facilitate the receipt of
                    supplies, I submit that heretofore I have been very successful in employing my
                    good offices with local authorities in securing shipment supplies to our troops
                    at San Antonio, but in view of the circumstances which have lately arisen and
                    the evident purpose of the superior Mexican authorities to force withdrawal of
                    American troops by creating difficulties as much as possible, I do not feel
                    quite sure that further shipments may be made over railroad for military use. I
                    have reason to believe, also, that prohibition of use of telegraph and landing
                    in towns or even passing over by aeroplanes is under consideration.
                    Circumstances seem to indicate that Carranza troops are concentrated around the
                    command of Colonel Brown pending settlement of demands for withdrawal of
                    troops.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
